@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========


    System door to enable other doors to add mail messages to the database

    If any errors occur in posting only the sysop with the watch window open
    will see the error messages.

    e.g.  say you have a weektop chart, the weektop generator could add the
    chart to the conference mail base.

    e.g.  Or set_suspect in combination with the log file extractor could
    e-mail the sysop the contents of the log file for a suspect users
    session

    e.g.  Could be used by a new user announcer to post messages.


@EndNode


@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    Usual door installation, copy to Mail_Add.HBBS to HBBS:Doors/Mail

    Then add the following lines to HBBS:Commands/System

    MailAdd_Type_1=HBBS
    MailAdd_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/Mail/Mail_Add.HBBS {N} {O}

    Other doors are now free to use this door.

@EndNode

@Node SystemOptions "SystemOptions"

  System Options
  ==============

    None

@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    Usage:

    DOOR_SystemDoor("Mail_Add","<options>");

    where <options> is described below

    * indicates a required paramater

    <msgfile> [TO <tohandle>] [FROM <fromhandle>] [CONF <confnum>]
    [FLAGS <flags>] [TYPE <type>] [EXPIRY <DD-MMM-YYYY<]
    [ACCESS <accesslevel>] [SUBJECT <subject text>]

    Option         Default                Function
    ==========================================================================
  * <msgfile>      None                   The path and filename of the message
                                          text.

    <tohandle>     Current Users Handle   The handle of the user to send the
                                          message to.

                                          Currently does not support posting
                                          to multiple users

    <fromhandle>   Current Users Handle   The handle to use in the FROM part
                                          of the message.  To which replies
                                          (if any) would be sent.

    <confnum>      Current Conf if the    Conference to post the message to.
                   user has joined one    Note, the Message Type cannot be
                                          anything other than "C" if this is
                                          specified.
    <Flags>        0 (Normal)             Flags are as follows.

                                          NORMAL        0
                                          PRIVATE       1
                                          NONDELETABLE  2
                                          MUSTREAD      4
                                          AUTODELETE    8
                                          *RESERVED*    16
                                          REMOVEFILES   32

                                          Add the numbers together to use
                                          more than one flag at the same time

    <Type>         C                      Specified the message type, one of:

                                          C - Conference Mail
                                          U - User Mail
                                          P - Public Mail
                                          S - Sysop Mail

                                          If type S then make sure ToHandle
                                          is the name of the sysop
                                          (see BBSGlobal->SysopAccount)

    <DD-MMM-YYYY>  No Expiry              The date after which the message
                                          is deemed to be expired.

    <AccessLevel>  0                      The user reading the message you
                                          are posting must have equal or
                                          higher access to read the message

    <Subject text> "<No Subject Defined>" Specifies the message subject
                                          NOTE: If this option is used it
                                          must be the last option in the
                                          options string.  Any options after
                                          it would be ignored.

    VERBOSE        NOVERBOSE              If the VERBOSE keyword is specified
                                          then information will be shown to
                                          the watch window.

    Example:


    DOOR_SystemDoor("Mail_Add","HBBS:Nodes/Node0/Work/NewMail.TXT"); // sends a message from the user to the user with
      // everything else set as default

    DOOR_SystemDoor("Mail_Add","HBBS:Nodes/Node0/Work/NewMail.TXT TO ALL FROM Hydra FLAGS 8 TYPE C CONF 4 SUBJECT THIS IS A TEST");


@EndNode

